# Sprint 1 — Auth backend

## Purpose

Implement **email/password** auth persisted in **Cloudflare D1**, expose **Next.js App Router** route handlers under `src/app/api/`, and issue **JWT access tokens** for the frontend PRD (`quizmaker_auth_token`). Work must use **`lib/d1-client.ts`** helpers, **positional SQL binds**, and **`const { env } = getCloudflareContext()`** for D1 and JWT secrets—**not** `process.env` alone in API routes.

---

## Ownership checks (future resources; Sprint 1 placeholder)

| Rule | Application |
|------|-------------|
| **Pattern** | Mutating or deleting domain rows (quizzes, items, etc.) must verify **`created_by` (or equivalent) === authenticated `userId`**. |
| **`userId` source** | Resolve from verified JWT **`sub`** claim (user id as stored in `users.id`). |
| **Sprint 1** | No quiz tables; document this contract in auth utilities (e.g. `requireUser(request)` returning `{ userId }`) so later routes import one helper. |
| **Alignment** | Matches **`.cursorrules`**: *Ownership: PUT/DELETE … must verify resource `created_by` matches the authenticated session `userId`.* |

